laboratory_examinations.findings: Confirmed SAH. The SAH was Grade II on the World Federation of Neurosurgical Societies scale and Grade 1 on the Fisher scale.
Showed a large complex right proximal MCA aneurysm and a smaller right distal MCA aneurysm, along with an aneurysm at the basilar tip and another on the superior cerebellar artery.

Revealed heavy calcification with 50% narrowing of both common carotid arteries just proximal to the carotid artery bulbs. The common femoral, external iliac, and internal iliac arteries were patent but exhibited reduced caliber, with an aortoiliac occlusion extending from just below the origin of the internal mesenteric artery to the external iliac artery origins bilaterally.

laboratory_examinations.procedure_name: MRI, MR angiography, and iv Dyna-CT scanning
laboratory_examinations.findings: The treated aneurysms are stable, and the untreated distal MCA aneurysm remains unchanged in size and configuration.
laboratory_examinations.changes_over_time: The untreated distal MCA aneurysm remains unchanged in size and configuration over 5 years.
